HEADWORD: Onus
<hw>O"nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>A
burden; an obligation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Onus probandi</b></col> <pr>(<?/)</pr> <ety>[L.]</ety>,
<cd>the obligation to furnish evidence to prove an assertion; the burden
of proof.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onward</ent>⟦br⟧
